title: "ChemistryLab.jl: Numerical laboratory for computational chemistry"
abstract: "Computational chemistry toolkit providing formula handling, species management, stoichiometric matrix construction, thermodynamic equilibrium via Gibbs free energy minimization, extended Debye-Hückel and Davies activity models, ideal and Redlich-Kister solid solution phases, interoperability with ThermoFun and Cemdata databases, and a kinetics module for mineral dissolution/precipitation coupled to ODE-based integration (Parrot-Killoh model, semi-adiabatic calorimetry). Initially focused on cement chemistry but applicable more broadly."
keywords:
  - "computational chemistry"
  - "Julia"
  - "chemical formulas"
  - "reactions"
  - "thermodynamic equilibrium"
  - "activity models"
  - "solid solutions"
  - "chemical kinetics"
  - "cement"
